## 1️⃣ Restaurant CRUD Schema (Firestore)

| Collection | Fields (type) | Notes |
|------------|---------------|-------|
| `restaurants` | `id: string`<br>`name: string`<br>`cuisine: string`<br>`address: string`<br>`lat: number`<br>`lng: number`<br>`hours: map`<br>`status: enum('active','inactive')`<br>`ownerUid: string` | Primary doc for each restaurant. |
| `restaurants/{id}/menus` | `itemId: string`<br>`name: string`<br>`description: string`<br>`price: number`<br>`imageUrl: string`<br>`modifiers: array` | Sub‑collection for menu items. |
| `restaurants/{id}/reviews` | `reviewId: string`<br>`userId: string`<br>`rating: number`<br>`comment: string`<br>`createdAt: timestamp` | Sub‑collection for reviews. |
| `restaurants/{id}/orders` | `orderId: string`<br>`customerId: string`<br>`status: enum('new','preparing','ready','delivering','delivered','cancelled')`<br>`total: number`<br>`items: array`<br>`createdAt: timestamp` | Sub‑collection for orders. |

**Security Rules** (draft, to be refined in the next sprint):

```firestore
rules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {
    // Authenticated users can read restaurant data
    match /restaurants/{restId} {
      allow read: if request.auth != null;

      // Only the restaurant owner can write to their own restaurant doc
      allow write: if request.auth != null &&
                   request.auth.uid == resource.data.ownerUid;

      // Admin portal writes (CRUD) are allowed via Cloud Functions
      // (to keep client rules simple)
    }
  }
}
```

> **Blocker?**  
> None. The schema is finalized and matches the admin portal UI we’re building next week.  

